# Feature Enhancements Walkthrough

All requested features have been successfully implemented! Here is a summary of the changes and how you can test them.

## 1. Database Data Deletion

> [!WARNING]
> **Action Required**: The database schemas for all microservices are currently configured to **drop and recreate** their data.
>
> 1. Please **stop all running backend terminal sessions** (Press `Ctrl + C`).
> 2. **Restart** all backend services (`mvn spring-boot:run`). This will drop all old data and create a fresh database.
> 3. After restarting once, you might want to manually revert `ddl-auto: create` back to `ddl-auto: update` in the `application.yml` files (located in `src/main/resources/` for each service) so your data persists on subsequent restarts.

## 2. Updated Routing & 1 Savings / 1 Current Limit

* **Routing**: After you register a new account, you will be seamlessly redirected to the Login page. Upon logging in, you'll land directly on the Dashboard.
* **Account Limits**: The `account-service` now strictly enforces business rules. If you attempt to open a second Savings or Current account, the backend will reject the request with a `400 Bad Request` and a clear error message.

## 3. User Profile & KYC Upload

A dedicated [Profile](file:///e:/Project/TransactSphere/frontend/src/pages/Profile.jsx) page has been built.
* Accessed via the "Profile" link in the Navbar.
* Displays your personal details, KYC status, and all active accounts.
* Includes an option to upload your KYC document directly. The document is converted to a secure Base64 format and stored in the PostgreSQL database.

## 4. Admin Dashboard

A secure [Admin Dashboard](file:///e:/Project/TransactSphere/frontend/src/pages/AdminDashboard.jsx) is now available at `/admin`.
* The dashboard displays the total number of registered customers.
* Admins can view the customer list, check their KYC status, and even view the uploaded KYC document via a direct link.
* **Approve / Reject functionality**: Action buttons are provided for pending KYCs, calling the new `PUT /api/v1/users/{userId}/kyc` endpoint in the `user-service`.
* *Security Note*: The Admin dashboard strictly focuses on user management and KYC. It does not fetch or have access to users' account balances.

## 5. Forgot Password & View Password Options

* **View Password**: Both the Registration and Login pages now feature an "Eye" icon to toggle password visibility.
* **Forgot Password**: The Login page includes a "Forgot Password?" link.
* The new [Forgot Password](file:///e:/Project/TransactSphere/frontend/src/pages/ForgotPassword.jsx) page securely asks for your `username` and `email`. If they match our records, it immediately updates your password in the `auth-service` database without requiring an external email provider setup.

## Next Steps

To verify these changes:
1. Restart your spring-boot applications in the terminal.
2. Register a new user and login.
3. Check out the Profile page and try uploading a KYC document.
4. Try creating multiple savings accounts.
5. Log out, use the Forgot Password flow to reset your credentials.
